      ],
      "source": "https://www.longislandguide.com/visit/islip/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In 1867 the Long Island Rail Road reached Islip, building its first depot and linking the town to the rest of Long Island.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        22
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islip%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Regular ferry service between Bay Shore and Fire Island began in 1862, making Islip a gateway to the Fire Island beaches.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
